WG REDWOOD <W.G.Redwood@bradford.ac.uk> writes:
 
>Please would somebody point me in the right direction for generating
>a one time pad from a user defined key???
 
Difficult to do securely...  You can use they key as an input to a PRNG, or
better yet, 'launder' the key via a hash function and/or a PRNG then use the
'laundered' output as the initialization for the PRNG...
 
Derek
